Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a model of distributed computing and proposes communication primitives to improve the round complexity of an algorithm.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a different approach to the MST problem and provides a tighter analysis of a special case of the sampling approach.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with graph algorithms and sampling techniques.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possible category as the paper deals with communication restrictions in a network model.
- cs.AL (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper deals with improving the round complexity of an algorithm.
